bool canReadAArch64SysReg ( MiscRegIndex  reg,
SCR  scr,
CPSR  cpsr,
ThreadContext *  tc 
)
bool ArmISA::canReadCoprocReg ( MiscRegIndex  reg,
SCR  scr,
CPSR  cpsr,
ThreadContext *  tc 
) 

01968 {
01969     bool secure = !scr.ns;
01970     bool canRead;
01971 
01972     switch (cpsr.mode) {
01973       case MODE_USER:
01974         canRead = secure ? miscRegInfo[reg][MISCREG_USR_S_RD] :
01975                            miscRegInfo[reg][MISCREG_USR_NS_RD];
01976         break;
01977       case MODE_FIQ:
01978       case MODE_IRQ:
01979       case MODE_SVC:
01980       case MODE_ABORT:
01981       case MODE_UNDEFINED:
01982       case MODE_SYSTEM:
01983         canRead = secure ? miscRegInfo[reg][MISCREG_PRI_S_RD] :
01984                            miscRegInfo[reg][MISCREG_PRI_NS_RD];
01985         break;
01986       case MODE_MON:
01987         canRead = secure ? miscRegInfo[reg][MISCREG_MON_NS0_RD] :
01988                            miscRegInfo[reg][MISCREG_MON_NS1_RD];
01989         break;
01990       case MODE_HYP:
01991         canRead = miscRegInfo[reg][MISCREG_HYP_RD];
01992         break;
01993       default:
01994         panic("Unrecognized mode setting in CPSR.\n");
01995     }
01996     // can't do permissions checkes on the root of a banked pair of regs
01997     assert(!miscRegInfo[reg][MISCREG_BANKED]);
01998     return canRead;
01999 }

) [inline, static] 

00193 {
00194     return (a1 < b1 ? -1 : a1 > b1 ? 1 : a0 < b0 ? -1 : a0 > b0 ? 1 : 0);
00195 }

00364         void
00365         advance()
00366         {
00367             Base::advance();
00368             flags = nextFlags;
00369             npc(pc() + (thumb() ? 2 : 4));
00370 
00371             if (_nextItstate) {
00372                 _itstate = _nextItstate;
00373                 _nextItstate = 0;
00374             } else if (_itstate) {
00375                 ITSTATE it = _itstate;
00376                 uint8_t cond_mask = it.mask;
00377                 uint8_t thumb_cond = it.cond;
00378                 DPRINTF(Decoder, "Advancing ITSTATE from %#x,%#x.\n",
00379                         thumb_cond, cond_mask);
00380                 cond_mask <<= 1;
00381                 uint8_t new_bit = bits(cond_mask, 4);
00382                 cond_mask &= mask(4);
00383                 if (cond_mask == 0)
00384                     thumb_cond = 0;
00385                 else
00386                     replaceBits(thumb_cond, 0, new_bit);
00387                 DPRINTF(Decoder, "Advancing ITSTATE to %#x,%#x.\n",
00388                         thumb_cond, cond_mask);
00389                 it.mask = cond_mask;
00390                 it.cond = thumb_cond;
00391                 _itstate = it;
00392             }
00393         }
00394

00396         uEnd()
00397         {
00398             advance();
00399             upc(0);
00400             nupc(1);
00401         }

00409         void
00410         instNPC(Addr val)
00411         {
00412             // @todo: review this when AArch32/64 interprocessing is
00413             // supported
00414             if (aarch64())
00415                 npc(val);  // AArch64 doesn't force PC alignment, a PC
00416                            // Alignment Fault can be raised instead
00417             else
00418                 npc(val &~ mask(nextThumb() ? 1 : 2));
00419         }
00420 
00421         Addr
00422         instNPC() const
00423         {
00424             return npc();
00425         }
00426 
00427         // Perform an interworking branch.
00428         void
00429         instIWNPC(Addr val)
00430         {
00431             bool thumbEE = (thumb() && jazelle());
00432 
00433             Addr newPC = val;
00434             if (thumbEE) {
00435                 if (bits(newPC, 0)) {
00436                     newPC = newPC & ~mask(1);
00437                 }  // else we have a bad interworking address; do not call
00438                    // panic() since the instruction could be executed
00439                    // speculatively
00440             } else {
00441                 if (bits(newPC, 0)) {
00442                     nextThumb(true);
00443                     newPC = newPC & ~mask(1);
00444                 } else if (!bits(newPC, 1)) {
00445                     nextThumb(false);
00446                 } else {
00447                     // This state is UNPREDICTABLE in the ARM architecture
00448                     // The easy thing to do is just mask off the bit and
00449                     // stay in the current mode, so we'll do that.
00450                     newPC &= ~mask(2);
00451                 }
00452             }
00453             npc(newPC);
00454         }
00455 
00456         // Perform an interworking branch in ARM mode, a regular branch
00457         // otherwise.
00458         void
00459         instAIWNPC(Addr val)
00460         {
00461             if (!thumb() && !jazelle())
00462                 instIWNPC(val);
00463             else
00464                 instNPC(val);
00465         }
00466

00468         operator == (const PCState &opc) const
00469         {
00470             return Base::operator == (opc) &&
00471                 flags == opc.flags && nextFlags == opc.nextFlags &&
00472                 _itstate == opc._itstate && _nextItstate == opc._nextItstate;
00473         }

00476         operator != (const PCState &opc) const

fpType ArmISA::fixDest ( bool  flush,
bool  defaultNan,
fpType  val,
fpType  op1,
fpType  op2 
) [inline] 

00237 {
00238     int fpClass = std::fpclassify(val);
00239     fpType junk = 0.0;
00240     if (fpClass == FP_NAN) {
00241         const bool single = (sizeof(val) == sizeof(float));
00242         const uint64_t qnan = single ? 0x7fc00000 : ULL(0x7ff8000000000000);
00243         const bool nan1 = std::isnan(op1);
00244         const bool nan2 = std::isnan(op2);
00245         const bool signal1 = nan1 && ((fpToBits(op1) & qnan) != qnan);
00246         const bool signal2 = nan2 && ((fpToBits(op2) & qnan) != qnan);
00247         if ((!nan1 && !nan2) || defaultNan) {
00248             val = bitsToFp(qnan, junk);
00249         } else if (signal1) {
00250             val = bitsToFp(fpToBits(op1) | qnan, junk);
00251         } else if (signal2) {
00252             val = bitsToFp(fpToBits(op2) | qnan, junk);
00253         } else if (nan1) {
00254             val = op1;
00255         } else if (nan2) {
00256             val = op2;
00257         }
00258     } else if (fpClass == FP_SUBNORMAL && flush) {
00259         // Turn val into a zero with the correct sign;
00260         uint64_t bitMask = ULL(0x1) << (sizeof(fpType) * 8 - 1);
00261         val = bitsToFp(fpToBits(val) & bitMask, junk);
00262         feclearexcept(FeInexact);
00263         feraiseexcept(FeUnderflow);
00264     }
00265     return val;
00266 }

static bool ArmISA::flushToZero ( fpType &  op  )  [inline, static] 

00119 {
00120     fpType junk = 0.0;
00121     if (std::fpclassify(op) == FP_SUBNORMAL) {
00122         uint64_t bitMask = ULL(0x1) << (sizeof(fpType) * 8 - 1);
00123         op = bitsToFp(fpToBits(op) & bitMask, junk);

static void ArmISA::fp128_normalise ( uint64_t *  mnt0,
uint64_t *  mnt1,
int *  exp 
) [inline, static] 

00253 {
00254     uint64_t x0 = *mnt0;
00255     uint64_t x1 = *mnt1;
00256     int shift;
00257 
00258     if (!x0 && !x1) {
00259         return;
00260     }
00261 
00262     if (!x1) {
00263         x1 = x0;
00264         x0 = 0;
00265         *exp -= 64;
00266     }
00267 
00268     for (shift = 32; shift; shift >>= 1) {
00269         if (!(x1 >> (64 - shift))) {
00270             x1 = x1 << shift | x0 >> (64 - shift);
00271             x0 <<= shift;
00272             *exp -= shift;
00273         }
00274     }
00275 
00276     *mnt0 = x0;
00277     *mnt1 = x1;
00278 }

static uint16_t ArmISA::fp16_normalise ( uint16_t  mnt,
int *  exp 
) [inline, static] 

00199 {
00200     int shift;
00201 
00202     if (!mnt) {
00203         return 0;
00204     }
00205 
00206     for (shift = 8; shift; shift >>= 1) {
00207         if (!(mnt >> (16 - shift))) {
00208             mnt <<= shift;
00209             *exp -= shift;
00210         }
00211     }
00212     return mnt;
00213 }

static uint16_t ArmISA::fp16_pack ( uint16_t  sgn,
uint16_t  exp,
uint16_t  mnt 
) [inline, static] 

00282 {
00283     return sgn << 15 | exp << 10 | (mnt & (((uint16_t)1 << 10) - 1));
00284 }

static uint16_t ArmISA::fp16_round_ ( int  sgn,
int  exp,
uint16_t  mnt,
int  rm,
int  mode,
int *  flags 
) [static] 

00553 {
00554     int biased_exp; // non-negative exponent value for result
00555     uint16_t int_mant; // mantissa for result, less than (1 << 11)
00556     int error; // 0, 1, 2 or 3, where 2 means int_mant is wrong by exactly 0.5
00557 
00558     assert(rm != FPRounding_TIEAWAY);
00559 
00560     // There is no flush to zero in this case!
00561 
00562     // The bottom 5 bits of mnt are orred together:
00563     mnt = (uint16_t)1 << 12 | mnt >> 4 | ((mnt & 31) != 0);
00564 
00565     if (exp > 0) {
00566         biased_exp = exp;
00567         int_mant = mnt >> 2;
00568         error = mnt & 3;
00569     } else {
00570         biased_exp = 0;
00571         int_mant = lsr16(mnt, 3 - exp);
00572         error = (lsr16(mnt, 1 - exp) & 3) | !!(mnt & (lsl16(1, 1 - exp) - 1));
00573     }
00574 
00575     if (!biased_exp && error) { // xx should also check fpscr_val<11>
00576         *flags |= FPLIB_UFC;
00577     }
00578 
00579     // Round up:
00580     if ((rm == FPLIB_RN && (error == 3 ||
00581                             (error == 2 && (int_mant & 1)))) ||
00582         (((rm == FPLIB_RP && !sgn) || (rm == FPLIB_RM && sgn)) && error)) {
00583         ++int_mant;
00584         if (int_mant == (uint32_t)1 << 10) {
00585             // Rounded up from denormalized to normalized
00586             biased_exp = 1;
00587         }
00588         if (int_mant == (uint32_t)1 << 11) {
00589             // Rounded up to next exponent
00590             ++biased_exp;
00591             int_mant >>= 1;
00592         }
00593     }
00594 
00595     // Handle rounding to odd aka Von Neumann rounding:
00596     if (error && rm == FPRounding_ODD)
00597         int_mant |= 1;
00598 
00599     // Handle overflow:
00600     if (!(mode & FPLIB_AHP)) {
00601         if (biased_exp >= 31) {
00602             *flags |= FPLIB_OFC | FPLIB_IXC;
00603             if (rm == FPLIB_RN || (rm == FPLIB_RP && !sgn) ||
00604                 (rm == FPLIB_RM && sgn)) {
00605                 return fp16_infinity(sgn);
00606             } else {
00607                 return fp16_max_normal(sgn);
00608             }
00609         }
00610     } else {
00611         if (biased_exp >= 32) {
00612             *flags |= FPLIB_IOC;
00613             return fp16_pack(sgn, 31, -1);
00614         }
00615     }
00616 
00617     if (error) {
00618         *flags |= FPLIB_IXC;
00619     }
00620 
00621     return fp16_pack(sgn, biased_exp, int_mant);
00622 }

static void ArmISA::fp16_unpack ( int *  sgn,
int *  exp,
uint16_t *  mnt,
uint16_t  x,
int  mode,
int *  flags 
) [inline, static] 

00373 {
00374     *sgn = x >> 15;
00375     *exp = x >> 10 & 31;
00376     *mnt = x & (((uint16_t)1 << 10) - 1);
00377 
00378     // Handle subnormals:
00379     if (*exp) {
00380         *mnt |= (uint16_t)1 << 10;
00381     } else {
00382         ++*exp;
00383         // There is no flush to zero in this case!
00384     }
00385 }

static uint16_t ArmISA::fp16_zero ( int  sgn  )  [inline, static] 

00300 {
00301     return fp16_pack(sgn, 0, 0);
00302 }

static uint32_t ArmISA::fp32_add ( uint32_t  a,
uint32_t  b,
int  neg,
int  mode,
int *  flags 
) [static] 

00916 {
00917     int a_sgn, a_exp, b_sgn, b_exp, x_sgn, x_exp;
00918     uint32_t a_mnt, b_mnt, x, x_mnt;
00919 
00920     fp32_unpack(&a_sgn, &a_exp, &a_mnt, a, mode, flags);
00921     fp32_unpack(&b_sgn, &b_exp, &b_mnt, b, mode, flags);
00922 
00923     if ((x = fp32_process_NaNs(a, b, mode, flags))) {
00924         return x;
00925     }
00926 
00927     b_sgn ^= neg;
00928 
00929     // Handle infinities and zeroes:
00930     if (a_exp == 255 && b_exp == 255 && a_sgn != b_sgn) {
00931         *flags |= FPLIB_IOC;
00932         return fp32_defaultNaN();
00933     } else if (a_exp == 255) {
00934         return fp32_infinity(a_sgn);
00935     } else if (b_exp == 255) {
00936         return fp32_infinity(b_sgn);
00937     } else if (!a_mnt && !b_mnt && a_sgn == b_sgn) {
00938         return fp32_zero(a_sgn);
00939     }
00940 
00941     a_mnt <<= 3;
00942     b_mnt <<= 3;
00943     if (a_exp >= b_exp) {
00944         b_mnt = (lsr32(b_mnt, a_exp - b_exp) |
00945                  !!(b_mnt & (lsl32(1, a_exp - b_exp) - 1)));
00946         b_exp = a_exp;
00947     } else {
00948         a_mnt = (lsr32(a_mnt, b_exp - a_exp) |
00949                  !!(a_mnt & (lsl32(1, b_exp - a_exp) - 1)));
00950         a_exp = b_exp;
00951     }
00952     x_sgn = a_sgn;
00953     x_exp = a_exp;
00954     if (a_sgn == b_sgn) {
00955         x_mnt = a_mnt + b_mnt;
00956     } else if (a_mnt >= b_mnt) {
00957         x_mnt = a_mnt - b_mnt;
00958     } else {
00959         x_sgn ^= 1;
00960         x_mnt = b_mnt - a_mnt;
00961     }
00962 
00963     if (!x_mnt) {
00964         // Sign of exact zero result depends on rounding mode
00965         return fp32_zero((mode & 3) == 2);
00966     }
00967 
00968     x_mnt = fp32_normalise(x_mnt, &x_exp);
00969 
00970     return fp32_round(x_sgn, x_exp + 5, x_mnt << 1, mode, flags);
00971 }

static int ArmISA::fp32_compare_eq ( uint32_t  a,
uint32_t  b,
int  mode,
int *  flags 
) [static] 

00778 {
00779     int a_sgn, a_exp, b_sgn, b_exp;
00780     uint32_t a_mnt, b_mnt;
00781 
00782     fp32_unpack(&a_sgn, &a_exp, &a_mnt, a, mode, flags);
00783     fp32_unpack(&b_sgn, &b_exp, &b_mnt, b, mode, flags);
00784 
00785     if ((a_exp == 255 && (uint32_t)(a_mnt << 9)) ||
00786         (b_exp == 255 && (uint32_t)(b_mnt << 9))) {
00787         if ((a_exp == 255 && (uint32_t)(a_mnt << 9) && !(a >> 22 & 1)) ||
00788             (b_exp == 255 && (uint32_t)(b_mnt << 9) && !(b >> 22 & 1)))
00789             *flags |= FPLIB_IOC;
00790         return 0;
00791     }
00792     return a == b || (!a_mnt && !b_mnt);
00793 }

static int ArmISA::fp32_compare_ge ( uint32_t  a,
uint32_t  b,

) [static] 

00797 {

00800

00802     fp32_unpack(&b_sgn, &b_exp, &b_mnt, b, mode, flags);
00803

00805         (b_exp == 255 && (uint32_t)(b_mnt << 9))) {

00807         return 0;

00818 }

static uint32_t ArmISA::fp32_cvtf ( uint64_t  a,
int  fbits,
int  u,
int  mode,
int *  flags 
) [static] 

03028 {
03029     int x_sgn = !u && a >> 63;
03030     int x_exp = 190 - fbits;
03031     uint64_t x_mnt = x_sgn ? -a : a;
03032 
03033     // Handle zero:
03034     if (!x_mnt) {
03035         return fp32_zero(0);
03036     }
03037 
03038     // Normalise and convert to 32 bits, collapsing error into bottom bit:
03039     x_mnt = fp64_normalise(x_mnt, &x_exp);

static uint32_t ArmISA::fp32_defaultNaN (  )  [inline, static]

static uint32_t ArmISA::fp32_div ( uint32_t  a,
uint32_t  b,
int  mode,
int *  flags 
) [static] 

01281 {
01282     int a_sgn, a_exp, b_sgn, b_exp, x_sgn, x_exp;
01283     uint32_t a_mnt, b_mnt, x;
01284     uint64_t x_mnt;
01285 
01286     fp32_unpack(&a_sgn, &a_exp, &a_mnt, a, mode, flags);
01287     fp32_unpack(&b_sgn, &b_exp, &b_mnt, b, mode, flags);
01288 
01289     if ((x = fp32_process_NaNs(a, b, mode, flags)))
01290         return x;
01291 
01292     // Handle infinities and zeroes:
01293     if ((a_exp == 255 && b_exp == 255) || (!a_mnt && !b_mnt)) {
01294         *flags |= FPLIB_IOC;
01295         return fp32_defaultNaN();
01296     }
01297     if (a_exp == 255 || !b_mnt) {
01298         if (a_exp != 255)
01299             *flags |= FPLIB_DZC;
01300         return fp32_infinity(a_sgn ^ b_sgn);
01301     }
01302     if (!a_mnt || b_exp == 255)
01303         return fp32_zero(a_sgn ^ b_sgn);
01304 
01305     // Divide, setting bottom bit if inexact:
01306     a_mnt = fp32_normalise(a_mnt, &a_exp);
01307     x_sgn = a_sgn ^ b_sgn;
01308     x_exp = a_exp - b_exp + 172;
01309     x_mnt = ((uint64_t)a_mnt << 18) / b_mnt;
01310     x_mnt |= (x_mnt * b_mnt != (uint64_t)a_mnt << 18);
01311 
01312     // Normalise and convert to 32 bits, collapsing error into bottom bit:
01313     x_mnt = fp64_normalise(x_mnt, &x_exp);
01314     x_mnt = x_mnt >> 31 | !!(uint32_t)(x_mnt << 1);
01315 
01316     return fp32_round(x_sgn, x_exp, x_mnt, mode, flags);
01317 }

static uint32_t ArmISA::fp32_mul ( uint32_t  a,
uint32_t  b,
int  mode,
int *  flags 
) [static] 

01034 {
01035     int a_sgn, a_exp, b_sgn, b_exp, x_sgn, x_exp;
01036     uint32_t a_mnt, b_mnt, x;
01037     uint64_t x_mnt;
01038 
01039     fp32_unpack(&a_sgn, &a_exp, &a_mnt, a, mode, flags);
01040     fp32_unpack(&b_sgn, &b_exp, &b_mnt, b, mode, flags);
01041 
01042     if ((x = fp32_process_NaNs(a, b, mode, flags))) {
01043         return x;
01044     }
01045 
01046     // Handle infinities and zeroes:
01047     if ((a_exp == 255 && !b_mnt) || (b_exp == 255 && !a_mnt)) {
01048         *flags |= FPLIB_IOC;
01049         return fp32_defaultNaN();
01050     } else if (a_exp == 255 || b_exp == 255) {
01051         return fp32_infinity(a_sgn ^ b_sgn);
01052     } else if (!a_mnt || !b_mnt) {
01053         return fp32_zero(a_sgn ^ b_sgn);
01054     }
01055 
01056     // Multiply and normalise:
01057     x_sgn = a_sgn ^ b_sgn;
01058     x_exp = a_exp + b_exp - 110;
01059     x_mnt = (uint64_t)a_mnt * b_mnt;
01060     x_mnt = fp64_normalise(x_mnt, &x_exp);
01061 
01062     // Convert to 32 bits, collapsing error into bottom bit:
01063     x_mnt = lsr64(x_mnt, 31) | !!lsl64(x_mnt, 33);
01064 
01065     return fp32_round(x_sgn, x_exp, x_mnt, mode, flags);
01066 }

static uint32_t ArmISA::fp32_muladd ( uint32_t  a,
uint32_t  b,
uint32_t  c,
int  scale,
int  mode,
int *  flags 
) [static] 

01107 {
01108     int a_sgn, a_exp, b_sgn, b_exp, c_sgn, c_exp, x_sgn, x_exp, y_sgn, y_exp;
01109     uint32_t a_mnt, b_mnt, c_mnt, x;
01110     uint64_t x_mnt, y_mnt;
01111 
01112     fp32_unpack(&a_sgn, &a_exp, &a_mnt, a, mode, flags);
01113     fp32_unpack(&b_sgn, &b_exp, &b_mnt, b, mode, flags);
01114     fp32_unpack(&c_sgn, &c_exp, &c_mnt, c, mode, flags);
01115 
01116     x = fp32_process_NaNs3(a, b, c, mode, flags);
01117 
01118     // Quiet NaN added to product of zero and infinity:
01119     if (a_exp == 255 && (a_mnt >> 22 & 1) &&
01120         ((!b_mnt && c_exp == 255 && !(uint32_t)(c_mnt << 9)) ||
01121          (!c_mnt && b_exp == 255 && !(uint32_t)(b_mnt << 9)))) {
01122         x = fp32_defaultNaN();
01123         *flags |= FPLIB_IOC;
01124     }
01125 
01126     if (x) {
01127         return x;
01128     }
01129 
01130     // Handle infinities and zeroes:
01131     if ((b_exp == 255 && !c_mnt) ||
01132         (c_exp == 255 && !b_mnt) ||
01133         (a_exp == 255 && (b_exp == 255 || c_exp == 255) &&
01134          (a_sgn != (b_sgn ^ c_sgn)))) {
01135         *flags |= FPLIB_IOC;
01136         return fp32_defaultNaN();
01137     }
01138     if (a_exp == 255)
01139         return fp32_infinity(a_sgn);
01140     if (b_exp == 255 || c_exp == 255)
01141         return fp32_infinity(b_sgn ^ c_sgn);
01142     if (!a_mnt && (!b_mnt || !c_mnt) && a_sgn == (b_sgn ^ c_sgn))
01143         return fp32_zero(a_sgn);
01144 
01145     x_sgn = a_sgn;
01146     x_exp = a_exp + 13;
01147     x_mnt = (uint64_t)a_mnt << 27;
01148 
01149     // Multiply:
01150     y_sgn = b_sgn ^ c_sgn;
01151     y_exp = b_exp + c_exp - 113;
01152     y_mnt = (uint64_t)b_mnt * c_mnt << 3;
01153     if (!y_mnt) {
01154         y_exp = x_exp;
01155     }
01156 
01157     // Add:
01158     if (x_exp >= y_exp) {
01159         y_mnt = (lsr64(y_mnt, x_exp - y_exp) |
01160                  !!(y_mnt & (lsl64(1, x_exp - y_exp) - 1)));
01161         y_exp = x_exp;
01162     } else {
01163         x_mnt = (lsr64(x_mnt, y_exp - x_exp) |
01164                  !!(x_mnt & (lsl64(1, y_exp - x_exp) - 1)));
01165         x_exp = y_exp;
01166     }
01167     if (x_sgn == y_sgn) {
01168         x_mnt = x_mnt + y_mnt;
01169     } else if (x_mnt >= y_mnt) {
01170         x_mnt = x_mnt - y_mnt;
01171     } else {
01172         x_sgn ^= 1;
01173         x_mnt = y_mnt - x_mnt;
01174     }
01175 
01176     if (!x_mnt) {
01177         // Sign of exact zero result depends on rounding mode
01178         return fp32_zero((mode & 3) == 2);
01179     }
01180 
01181     // Normalise and convert to 32 bits, collapsing error into bottom bit:
01182     x_mnt = fp64_normalise(x_mnt, &x_exp);
01183     x_mnt = x_mnt >> 31 | !!(uint32_t)(x_mnt << 1);
01184 
01185     return fp32_round(x_sgn, x_exp + scale, x_mnt, mode, flags);
01186 }

static uint32_t ArmISA::fp32_normalise ( uint32_t  mnt,
int *  exp 
) [inline, static] 

00217 {
00218     int shift;
00219 
00220     if (!mnt) {
00221         return 0;
00222     }
00223 
00224     for (shift = 16; shift; shift >>= 1) {
00225         if (!(mnt >> (32 - shift))) {
00226             mnt <<= shift;
00227             *exp -= shift;
00228         }
00229     }
00230     return mnt;
00231 }

static uint32_t ArmISA::fp32_pack ( uint32_t  sgn,

) [inline, static] 

00288 {

static uint32_t ArmISA::fp32_process_NaN ( uint32_t  a,
int  mode,
int *  flags 
) [inline, static] 

00429 {
00430     if (!(a >> 22 & 1)) {
00431         *flags |= FPLIB_IOC;
00432         a |= (uint32_t)1 << 22;
00433     }

static uint32_t ArmISA::fp32_process_NaNs ( uint32_t  a,
uint32_t  b,
int  mode,
int *  flags 
) [static] 

00449 {
00450     int a_exp = a >> 23 & 255;
00451     uint32_t a_mnt = a & (((uint32_t)1 << 23) - 1);
00452     int b_exp = b >> 23 & 255;
00453     uint32_t b_mnt = b & (((uint32_t)1 << 23) - 1);
00454 
00455     // Handle signalling NaNs:
00456     if (a_exp == 255 && a_mnt && !(a_mnt >> 22 & 1))
00457         return fp32_process_NaN(a, mode, flags);
00458     if (b_exp == 255 && b_mnt && !(b_mnt >> 22 & 1))
00459         return fp32_process_NaN(b, mode, flags);
00460 
00461     // Handle quiet NaNs:
00462     if (a_exp == 255 && a_mnt)
00463         return fp32_process_NaN(a, mode, flags);
00464     if (b_exp == 255 && b_mnt)
00465         return fp32_process_NaN(b, mode, flags);
00466 
00467     return 0;
00468 }

00495 {

00499     uint32_t b_mnt = b & (((uint32_t)1 << 23) - 1);

static uint32_t ArmISA::fp32_round ( int  sgn,
int  exp,
uint32_t  mnt,
int  mode,
int *  flags 
) [static] 

00696 {

static uint32_t ArmISA::fp32_round_ ( int  sgn,
int  exp,
uint32_t  mnt,
int  rm,
int  mode,
int *  flags 
) [static] 

00626 {
00627     int biased_exp; // non-negative exponent value for result
00628     uint32_t int_mant; // mantissa for result, less than (1 << 24)
00629     int error; // 0, 1, 2 or 3, where 2 means int_mant is wrong by exactly 0.5
00630 
00631     assert(rm != FPRounding_TIEAWAY);
00632 
00633     // Flush to zero:
00634     if ((mode & FPLIB_FZ) && exp < 1) {
00635         *flags |= FPLIB_UFC;
00636         return fp32_zero(sgn);
00637     }
00638 
00639     // The bottom 8 bits of mnt are orred together:
00640     mnt = (uint32_t)1 << 25 | mnt >> 7 | ((mnt & 255) != 0);
00641 
00642     if (exp > 0) {
00643         biased_exp = exp;
00644         int_mant = mnt >> 2;
00645         error = mnt & 3;
00646     } else {
00647         biased_exp = 0;
00648         int_mant = lsr32(mnt, 3 - exp);
00649         error = (lsr32(mnt, 1 - exp) & 3) | !!(mnt & (lsl32(1, 1 - exp) - 1));
00650     }
00651 
00652     if (!biased_exp && error) { // xx should also check fpscr_val<11>
00653         *flags |= FPLIB_UFC;
00654     }
00655 
00656     // Round up:
00657     if ((rm == FPLIB_RN && (error == 3 ||
00658                             (error == 2 && (int_mant & 1)))) ||
00659         (((rm == FPLIB_RP && !sgn) || (rm == FPLIB_RM && sgn)) && error)) {
00660         ++int_mant;
00661         if (int_mant == (uint32_t)1 << 23) {
00662             // Rounded up from denormalized to normalized
00663             biased_exp = 1;
00664         }
00665         if (int_mant == (uint32_t)1 << 24) {
00666             // Rounded up to next exponent
00667             ++biased_exp;
00668             int_mant >>= 1;
00669         }
00670     }
00671 
00672     // Handle rounding to odd aka Von Neumann rounding:
00673     if (error && rm == FPRounding_ODD)
00674         int_mant |= 1;
00675 
00676     // Handle overflow:
00677     if (biased_exp >= 255) {
00678         *flags |= FPLIB_OFC | FPLIB_IXC;
00679         if (rm == FPLIB_RN || (rm == FPLIB_RP && !sgn) ||
00680             (rm == FPLIB_RM && sgn)) {
00681             return fp32_infinity(sgn);
00682         } else {
00683             return fp32_max_normal(sgn);
00684         }
00685     }
00686 
00687     if (error) {
00688         *flags |= FPLIB_IXC;
00689     }
00690 
00691     return fp32_pack(sgn, biased_exp, int_mant);
00692 }

static uint32_t ArmISA::fp32_sqrt ( uint32_t  a,
int  mode,
int *  flags 
) [static] 

01398 {
01399     int a_sgn, a_exp, x_sgn, x_exp;
01400     uint32_t a_mnt, x, x_mnt;
01401     uint64_t t0, t1;
01402 
01403     fp32_unpack(&a_sgn, &a_exp, &a_mnt, a, mode, flags);
01404 
01405     // Handle NaNs:
01406     if (a_exp == 255 && (uint32_t)(a_mnt << 9))
01407         return fp32_process_NaN(a, mode, flags);
01408 
01409     // Handle infinities and zeroes:
01410     if (!a_mnt) {
01411         return fp32_zero(a_sgn);
01412     }
01413     if (a_exp == 255 && !a_sgn) {
01414         return fp32_infinity(a_sgn);
01415     }
01416     if (a_sgn) {
01417         *flags |= FPLIB_IOC;
01418         return fp32_defaultNaN();
01419     }
01420 
01421     a_mnt = fp32_normalise(a_mnt, &a_exp);
01422     if (!(a_exp & 1)) {
01423         ++a_exp;
01424         a_mnt >>= 1;
01425     }
01426 
01427     // x = (a * 3 + 5) / 8
01428     x = (a_mnt >> 2) + (a_mnt >> 3) + (5 << 28);
01429 
01430     // x = (a / x + x) / 2; // 16-bit accuracy
01431     x = (a_mnt / (x >> 15) + (x >> 16)) << 15;
01432 
01433     // x = (a / x + x) / 2; // 16-bit accuracy
01434     x = (a_mnt / (x >> 15) + (x >> 16)) << 15;
01435 
01436     // x = (a / x + x) / 2; // 32-bit accuracy
01437     x = ((((uint64_t)a_mnt << 32) / x) >> 2) + (x >> 1);
01438 
01439     x_sgn = 0;
01440     x_exp = (a_exp + 147) >> 1;
01441     x_mnt = ((x - (1 << 5)) >> 6) + 1;
01442     t1 = (uint64_t)x_mnt * x_mnt;
01443     t0 = (uint64_t)a_mnt << 19;
01444     if (t1 > t0) {
01445         --x_mnt;
01446     }
01447 
01448     x_mnt = fp32_normalise(x_mnt, &x_exp);
01449 
01450     return fp32_round(x_sgn, x_exp, x_mnt << 1 | (t1 != t0), mode, flags);
01451 }

static void ArmISA::fp32_unpack ( int *  sgn,
int *  exp,
uint32_t *  mnt,
uint32_t  x,
int  mode,
int *  flags 
) [inline, static] 

00390 {
00391     *sgn = x >> 31;
00392     *exp = x >> 23 & 255;
00393     *mnt = x & (((uint32_t)1 << 23) - 1);
00394 
00395     // Handle subnormals:
00396     if (*exp) {
00397         *mnt |= (uint32_t)1 << 23;
00398     } else {
00399         ++*exp;
00400         if ((mode & FPLIB_FZ) && *mnt) {
00401             *flags |= FPLIB_IDC;
00402             *mnt = 0;
00403         }
00404     }
00405 }

static uint32_t ArmISA::fp32_zero ( int  sgn  )  [inline, static] 

00306 {
00307     return fp32_pack(sgn, 0, 0);

static uint64_t ArmISA::fp64_add ( uint64_t  a,
uint64_t  b,
int  neg,
int  mode,
int *  flags 
) [static] 

00975 {
00976     int a_sgn, a_exp, b_sgn, b_exp, x_sgn, x_exp;
00977     uint64_t a_mnt, b_mnt, x, x_mnt;
00978 
00979     fp64_unpack(&a_sgn, &a_exp, &a_mnt, a, mode, flags);
00980     fp64_unpack(&b_sgn, &b_exp, &b_mnt, b, mode, flags);
00981 
00982     if ((x = fp64_process_NaNs(a, b, mode, flags))) {
00983         return x;
00984     }
00985 
00986     b_sgn ^= neg;
00987 
00988     // Handle infinities and zeroes:
00989     if (a_exp == 2047 && b_exp == 2047 && a_sgn != b_sgn) {
00990         *flags |= FPLIB_IOC;
00991         return fp64_defaultNaN();
00992     } else if (a_exp == 2047) {
00993         return fp64_infinity(a_sgn);
00994     } else if (b_exp == 2047) {
00995         return fp64_infinity(b_sgn);
00996     } else if (!a_mnt && !b_mnt && a_sgn == b_sgn) {
00997         return fp64_zero(a_sgn);
00998     }
00999 
01000     a_mnt <<= 3;
01001     b_mnt <<= 3;
01002     if (a_exp >= b_exp) {
01003         b_mnt = (lsr64(b_mnt, a_exp - b_exp) |
01004                  !!(b_mnt & (lsl64(1, a_exp - b_exp) - 1)));
01005         b_exp = a_exp;
01006     } else {
01007         a_mnt = (lsr64(a_mnt, b_exp - a_exp) |
01008                  !!(a_mnt & (lsl64(1, b_exp - a_exp) - 1)));
01009         a_exp = b_exp;
01010     }
01011     x_sgn = a_sgn;
01012     x_exp = a_exp;
01013     if (a_sgn == b_sgn) {
01014         x_mnt = a_mnt + b_mnt;
01015     } else if (a_mnt >= b_mnt) {
01016         x_mnt = a_mnt - b_mnt;
01017     } else {
01018         x_sgn ^= 1;
01019         x_mnt = b_mnt - a_mnt;
01020     }
01021 
01022     if (!x_mnt) {
01023         // Sign of exact zero result depends on rounding mode
01024         return fp64_zero((mode & 3) == 2);
01025     }
01026 
01027     x_mnt = fp64_normalise(x_mnt, &x_exp);
01028 
01029     return fp64_round(x_sgn, x_exp + 8, x_mnt << 1, mode, flags);
01030 }

static int ArmISA::fp64_compare_eq ( uint64_t  a,
uint64_t  b,

) [static] 

00847 {
00848     int a_sgn, a_exp, b_sgn, b_exp;

00850

00852     fp64_unpack(&b_sgn, &b_exp, &b_mnt, b, mode, flags);
00853

00855         (b_exp == 2047 && (uint64_t)(b_mnt << 12))) {

) [static]

static uint64_t ArmISA::fp64_cvtf ( uint64_t  a,

03047 {

static uint64_t ArmISA::fp64_div ( uint64_t  a,
uint64_t  b,
int  mode,
int *  flags 
) [static] 

01321 {
01322     int a_sgn, a_exp, b_sgn, b_exp, x_sgn, x_exp, c;
01323     uint64_t a_mnt, b_mnt, x, x_mnt, x0_mnt, x1_mnt;
01324 
01325     fp64_unpack(&a_sgn, &a_exp, &a_mnt, a, mode, flags);
01326     fp64_unpack(&b_sgn, &b_exp, &b_mnt, b, mode, flags);
01327 
01328     if ((x = fp64_process_NaNs(a, b, mode, flags)))
01329         return x;
01330 
01331     // Handle infinities and zeroes:
01332     if ((a_exp == 2047 && b_exp == 2047) || (!a_mnt && !b_mnt)) {
01333         *flags |= FPLIB_IOC;
01334         return fp64_defaultNaN();
01335     }
01336     if (a_exp == 2047 || !b_mnt) {
01337         if (a_exp != 2047)
01338             *flags |= FPLIB_DZC;
01339         return fp64_infinity(a_sgn ^ b_sgn);
01340     }
01341     if (!a_mnt || b_exp == 2047)
01342         return fp64_zero(a_sgn ^ b_sgn);
01343 
01344     // Find reciprocal of divisor with Newton-Raphson:
01345     a_mnt = fp64_normalise(a_mnt, &a_exp);
01346     b_mnt = fp64_normalise(b_mnt, &b_exp);
01347     x_mnt = ~(uint64_t)0 / (b_mnt >> 31);
01348     mul64x32(&x0_mnt, &x1_mnt, b_mnt, x_mnt);
01349     sub128(&x0_mnt, &x1_mnt, 0, (uint64_t)1 << 32, x0_mnt, x1_mnt);
01350     lsr128(&x0_mnt, &x1_mnt, x0_mnt, x1_mnt, 32);
01351     mul64x32(&x0_mnt, &x1_mnt, x0_mnt, x_mnt);
01352     lsr128(&x0_mnt, &x1_mnt, x0_mnt, x1_mnt, 33);
01353 
01354     // Multiply by dividend:
01355     x_sgn = a_sgn ^ b_sgn;
01356     x_exp = a_exp - b_exp + 1031;
01357     mul62x62(&x0_mnt, &x1_mnt, x0_mnt, a_mnt >> 2); // xx 62x62 is enough
01358     lsr128(&x0_mnt, &x1_mnt, x0_mnt, x1_mnt, 4);
01359     x_mnt = x1_mnt;
01360 
01361     // This is an underestimate, so try adding one:
01362     mul62x62(&x0_mnt, &x1_mnt, b_mnt >> 2, x_mnt + 1); // xx 62x62 is enough
01363     c = cmp128(x0_mnt, x1_mnt, 0, a_mnt >> 11);
01364     if (c <= 0) {
01365         ++x_mnt;
01366     }
01367 
01368     x_mnt = fp64_normalise(x_mnt, &x_exp);
01369 
01370     return fp64_round(x_sgn, x_exp, x_mnt << 1 | !!c, mode, flags);
01371 }

static uint64_t ArmISA::fp64_mul ( uint64_t  a,
uint64_t  b,
int  mode,
int *  flags 
) [static] 

01070 {
01071     int a_sgn, a_exp, b_sgn, b_exp, x_sgn, x_exp;
01072     uint64_t a_mnt, b_mnt, x;
01073     uint64_t x0_mnt, x1_mnt;
01074 
01075     fp64_unpack(&a_sgn, &a_exp, &a_mnt, a, mode, flags);
01076     fp64_unpack(&b_sgn, &b_exp, &b_mnt, b, mode, flags);
01077 
01078     if ((x = fp64_process_NaNs(a, b, mode, flags))) {
01079         return x;
01080     }
01081 
01082     // Handle infinities and zeroes:
01083     if ((a_exp == 2047 && !b_mnt) || (b_exp == 2047 && !a_mnt)) {
01084         *flags |= FPLIB_IOC;
01085         return fp64_defaultNaN();
01086     } else if (a_exp == 2047 || b_exp == 2047) {
01087         return fp64_infinity(a_sgn ^ b_sgn);
01088     } else if (!a_mnt || !b_mnt) {
01089         return fp64_zero(a_sgn ^ b_sgn);
01090     }
01091 
01092     // Multiply and normalise:
01093     x_sgn = a_sgn ^ b_sgn;
01094     x_exp = a_exp + b_exp - 1000;
01095     mul62x62(&x0_mnt, &x1_mnt, a_mnt, b_mnt);
01096     fp128_normalise(&x0_mnt, &x1_mnt, &x_exp);
01097 
01098     // Convert to 64 bits, collapsing error into bottom bit:
01099     x0_mnt = x1_mnt << 1 | !!x0_mnt;
01100 
01101     return fp64_round(x_sgn, x_exp, x0_mnt, mode, flags);
01102 }

static uint64_t ArmISA::fp64_muladd ( uint64_t  a,
uint64_t  b,
uint64_t  c,
int  scale,
int  mode,
int *  flags 
) [static] 

01191 {
01192     int a_sgn, a_exp, b_sgn, b_exp, c_sgn, c_exp, x_sgn, x_exp, y_sgn, y_exp;
01193     uint64_t a_mnt, b_mnt, c_mnt, x;
01194     uint64_t x0_mnt, x1_mnt, y0_mnt, y1_mnt;
01195 
01196     fp64_unpack(&a_sgn, &a_exp, &a_mnt, a, mode, flags);
01197     fp64_unpack(&b_sgn, &b_exp, &b_mnt, b, mode, flags);
01198     fp64_unpack(&c_sgn, &c_exp, &c_mnt, c, mode, flags);
01199 
01200     x = fp64_process_NaNs3(a, b, c, mode, flags);
01201 
01202     // Quiet NaN added to product of zero and infinity:
01203     if (a_exp == 2047 && (a_mnt >> 51 & 1) &&
01204         ((!b_mnt && c_exp == 2047 && !(uint64_t)(c_mnt << 12)) ||
01205          (!c_mnt && b_exp == 2047 && !(uint64_t)(b_mnt << 12)))) {
01206         x = fp64_defaultNaN();
01207         *flags |= FPLIB_IOC;
01208     }
01209 
01210     if (x) {
01211         return x;
01212     }
01213 
01214     // Handle infinities and zeroes:
01215     if ((b_exp == 2047 && !c_mnt) ||
01216         (c_exp == 2047 && !b_mnt) ||
01217         (a_exp == 2047 && (b_exp == 2047 || c_exp == 2047) &&
01218          (a_sgn != (b_sgn ^ c_sgn)))) {
01219         *flags |= FPLIB_IOC;
01220         return fp64_defaultNaN();
01221     }
01222     if (a_exp == 2047)
01223         return fp64_infinity(a_sgn);
01224     if (b_exp == 2047 || c_exp == 2047)
01225         return fp64_infinity(b_sgn ^ c_sgn);
01226     if (!a_mnt && (!b_mnt || !c_mnt) && a_sgn == (b_sgn ^ c_sgn))
01227         return fp64_zero(a_sgn);
01228 
01229     x_sgn = a_sgn;
01230     x_exp = a_exp + 11;
01231     x0_mnt = 0;
01232     x1_mnt = a_mnt;
01233 
01234     // Multiply:
01235     y_sgn = b_sgn ^ c_sgn;
01236     y_exp = b_exp + c_exp - 1003;
01237     mul62x62(&y0_mnt, &y1_mnt, b_mnt, c_mnt << 3);
01238     if (!y0_mnt && !y1_mnt) {
01239         y_exp = x_exp;
01240     }
01241 
01242     // Add:
01243     if (x_exp >= y_exp) {
01244         uint64_t t0, t1;
01245         lsl128(&t0, &t1, y0_mnt, y1_mnt,
01246                x_exp - y_exp < 128 ? 128 - (x_exp - y_exp) : 0);
01247         lsr128(&y0_mnt, &y1_mnt, y0_mnt, y1_mnt, x_exp - y_exp);
01248         y0_mnt |= !!(t0 | t1);
01249         y_exp = x_exp;
01250     } else {
01251         uint64_t t0, t1;
01252         lsl128(&t0, &t1, x0_mnt, x1_mnt,
01253                y_exp - x_exp < 128 ? 128 - (y_exp - x_exp) : 0);
01254         lsr128(&x0_mnt, &x1_mnt, x0_mnt, x1_mnt, y_exp - x_exp);
01255         x0_mnt |= !!(t0 | t1);
01256         x_exp = y_exp;
01257     }
01258     if (x_sgn == y_sgn) {
01259         add128(&x0_mnt, &x1_mnt, x0_mnt, x1_mnt, y0_mnt, y1_mnt);
01260     } else if (cmp128(x0_mnt, x1_mnt, y0_mnt, y1_mnt) >= 0) {
01261         sub128(&x0_mnt, &x1_mnt, x0_mnt, x1_mnt, y0_mnt, y1_mnt);
01262     } else {
01263         x_sgn ^= 1;
01264         sub128(&x0_mnt, &x1_mnt, y0_mnt, y1_mnt, x0_mnt, x1_mnt);
01265     }
01266 
01267     if (!x0_mnt && !x1_mnt) {
01268         // Sign of exact zero result depends on rounding mode
01269         return fp64_zero((mode & 3) == 2);
01270     }
01271 
01272     // Normalise and convert to 64 bits, collapsing error into bottom bit:
01273     fp128_normalise(&x0_mnt, &x1_mnt, &x_exp);
01274     x0_mnt = x1_mnt << 1 | !!x0_mnt;
01275 
01276     return fp64_round(x_sgn, x_exp + scale, x0_mnt, mode, flags);
01277 }

static uint64_t ArmISA::fp64_normalise ( uint64_t  mnt,
int *  exp 
) [inline, static] 

00235 {
00236     int shift;
00237 
00238     if (!mnt) {
00239         return 0;
00240     }
00241 
00242     for (shift = 32; shift; shift >>= 1) {
00243         if (!(mnt >> (64 - shift))) {
00244             mnt <<= shift;
00245             *exp -= shift;
00246         }
00247     }
00248     return mnt;
00249 }

00439 {

static uint64_t ArmISA::fp64_process_NaNs ( uint64_t  a,
uint64_t  b,
int  mode,
int *  flags 
) [static] 

00472 {
00473     int a_exp = a >> 52 & 2047;
00474     uint64_t a_mnt = a & (((uint64_t)1 << 52) - 1);
00475     int b_exp = b >> 52 & 2047;
00476     uint64_t b_mnt = b & (((uint64_t)1 << 52) - 1);
00477 
00478     // Handle signalling NaNs:
00479     if (a_exp == 2047 && a_mnt && !(a_mnt >> 51 & 1))
00480         return fp64_process_NaN(a, mode, flags);
00481     if (b_exp == 2047 && b_mnt && !(b_mnt >> 51 & 1))
00482         return fp64_process_NaN(b, mode, flags);
00483 
00484     // Handle quiet NaNs:
00485     if (a_exp == 2047 && a_mnt)
00486         return fp64_process_NaN(a, mode, flags);
00487     if (b_exp == 2047 && b_mnt)
00488         return fp64_process_NaN(b, mode, flags);
00489 
00490     return 0;
00491 }

static uint64_t ArmISA::fp64_process_NaNs3 ( uint64_t  a,
uint64_t  b,
uint64_t  c,
int  mode,
int *  flags 
) [static] 

00524 {
00525     int a_exp = a >> 52 & 2047;
00526     uint64_t a_mnt = a & (((uint64_t)1 << 52) - 1);
00527     int b_exp = b >> 52 & 2047;
00528     uint64_t b_mnt = b & (((uint64_t)1 << 52) - 1);
00529     int c_exp = c >> 52 & 2047;
00530     uint64_t c_mnt = c & (((uint64_t)1 << 52) - 1);
00531 
00532     // Handle signalling NaNs:
00533     if (a_exp == 2047 && a_mnt && !(a_mnt >> 51 & 1))
00534         return fp64_process_NaN(a, mode, flags);
00535     if (b_exp == 2047 && b_mnt && !(b_mnt >> 51 & 1))
00536         return fp64_process_NaN(b, mode, flags);
00537     if (c_exp == 2047 && c_mnt && !(c_mnt >> 51 & 1))
00538         return fp64_process_NaN(c, mode, flags);
00539 
00540     // Handle quiet NaNs:
00541     if (a_exp == 2047 && a_mnt)
00542         return fp64_process_NaN(a, mode, flags);
00543     if (b_exp == 2047 && b_mnt)
00544         return fp64_process_NaN(b, mode, flags);
00545     if (c_exp == 2047 && c_mnt)
00546         return fp64_process_NaN(c, mode, flags);
00547 
00548     return 0;
00549 }

static uint64_t ArmISA::fp64_repack ( int  sgn,
int  exp,
uint64_t  mnt 
) [static] 

02079 {
02080     return fp64_pack(sgn, mnt >> 52 ? exp : 0, mnt);
02081 }

static uint64_t ArmISA::fp64_round ( int  sgn,
int  exp,
uint64_t  mnt,
int  mode,
int *  flags 
) [static] 

00772 {
00773     return fp64_round_(sgn, exp, mnt, mode & 3, mode, flags);
00774 }

static uint64_t ArmISA::fp64_round_ ( int  sgn,
int  exp,
uint64_t  mnt,
int  rm,
int  mode,
int *  flags 
) [static] 

00702 {
00703     int biased_exp; // non-negative exponent value for result
00704     uint64_t int_mant; // mantissa for result, less than (1 << 52)
00705     int error; // 0, 1, 2 or 3, where 2 means int_mant is wrong by exactly 0.5
00706 
00707     assert(rm != FPRounding_TIEAWAY);
00708 
00709     // Flush to zero:
00710     if ((mode & FPLIB_FZ) && exp < 1) {
00711         *flags |= FPLIB_UFC;
00712         return fp64_zero(sgn);
00713     }
00714 
00715     // The bottom 11 bits of mnt are orred together:
00716     mnt = (uint64_t)1 << 54 | mnt >> 10 | ((mnt & 0x3ff) != 0);
00717 
00718     if (exp > 0) {
00719         biased_exp = exp;
00720         int_mant = mnt >> 2;
00721         error = mnt & 3;
00722     } else {
00723         biased_exp = 0;
00724         int_mant = lsr64(mnt, 3 - exp);
00725         error = (lsr64(mnt, 1 - exp) & 3) | !!(mnt & (lsl64(1, 1 - exp) - 1));
00726     }
00727 
00728     if (!biased_exp && error) { // xx should also check fpscr_val<11>
00729         *flags |= FPLIB_UFC;
00730     }
00731 
00732     // Round up:
00733     if ((rm == FPLIB_RN && (error == 3 ||
00734                             (error == 2 && (int_mant & 1)))) ||
00735         (((rm == FPLIB_RP && !sgn) || (rm == FPLIB_RM && sgn)) && error)) {
00736         ++int_mant;
00737         if (int_mant == (uint64_t)1 << 52) {
00738             // Rounded up from denormalized to normalized
00739             biased_exp = 1;
00740         }
00741         if (int_mant == (uint64_t)1 << 53) {
00742             // Rounded up to next exponent
00743             ++biased_exp;
00744             int_mant >>= 1;
00745         }
00746     }
00747 
00748     // Handle rounding to odd aka Von Neumann rounding:
00749     if (error && rm == FPRounding_ODD)
00750         int_mant |= 1;
00751 
00752     // Handle overflow:
00753     if (biased_exp >= 2047) {
00754         *flags |= FPLIB_OFC | FPLIB_IXC;
00755         if (rm == FPLIB_RN || (rm == FPLIB_RP && !sgn) ||
00756             (rm == FPLIB_RM && sgn)) {
00757             return fp64_infinity(sgn);
00758         } else {
00759             return fp64_max_normal(sgn);
00760         }
00761     }
00762 
00763     if (error) {
00764         *flags |= FPLIB_IXC;
00765     }
00766 
00767     return fp64_pack(sgn, biased_exp, int_mant);
00768 }

static uint64_t ArmISA::fp64_sqrt ( uint64_t  a,
int  mode,
int *  flags 
) [static] 

01455 {
01456     int a_sgn, a_exp, x_sgn, x_exp, c;
01457     uint64_t a_mnt, x_mnt, r, x0, x1;
01458     uint32_t x;
01459 
01460     fp64_unpack(&a_sgn, &a_exp, &a_mnt, a, mode, flags);
01461 
01462     // Handle NaNs:
01463     if (a_exp == 2047 && (uint64_t)(a_mnt << 12)) {
01464         return fp64_process_NaN(a, mode, flags);
01465     }
01466 
01467     // Handle infinities and zeroes:
01468     if (!a_mnt)
01469         return fp64_zero(a_sgn);
01470     if (a_exp == 2047 && !a_sgn)
01471         return fp64_infinity(a_sgn);
01472     if (a_sgn) {
01473         *flags |= FPLIB_IOC;
01474         return fp64_defaultNaN();
01475     }
01476 
01477     a_mnt = fp64_normalise(a_mnt, &a_exp);
01478     if (a_exp & 1) {
01479         ++a_exp;
01480         a_mnt >>= 1;
01481     }
01482 
01483     // x = (a * 3 + 5) / 8
01484     x = (a_mnt >> 34) + (a_mnt >> 35) + (5 << 28);
01485 
01486     // x = (a / x + x) / 2; // 16-bit accuracy
01487     x = ((a_mnt >> 32) / (x >> 15) + (x >> 16)) << 15;
01488 
01489     // x = (a / x + x) / 2; // 16-bit accuracy
01490     x = ((a_mnt >> 32) / (x >> 15) + (x >> 16)) << 15;
01491 
01492     // x = (a / x + x) / 2; // 32-bit accuracy
01493     x = ((a_mnt / x) >> 2) + (x >> 1);
01494 
01495     // r = 1 / x; // 32-bit accuracy
01496     r = ((uint64_t)1 << 62) / x;
01497 
01498     // r = r * (2 - x * r); // 64-bit accuracy
01499     mul64x32(&x0, &x1, -(uint64_t)x * r << 1, r);
01500     lsr128(&x0, &x1, x0, x1, 31);
01501 
01502     // x = (x + a * r) / 2; // 64-bit accuracy
01503     mul62x62(&x0, &x1, a_mnt >> 10, x0 >> 2);
01504     lsl128(&x0, &x1, x0, x1, 5);
01505     lsr128(&x0, &x1, x0, x1, 56);
01506 
01507     x0 = ((uint64_t)x << 31) + (x0 >> 1);
01508 
01509     x_sgn = 0;
01510     x_exp = (a_exp + 1053) >> 1;
01511     x_mnt = x0;
01512     x_mnt = ((x_mnt - (1 << 8)) >> 9) + 1;
01513     mul62x62(&x0, &x1, x_mnt, x_mnt);
01514     lsl128(&x0, &x1, x0, x1, 19);
01515     c = cmp128(x0, x1, 0, a_mnt);
01516     if (c > 0)
01517         --x_mnt;
01518 
01519     x_mnt = fp64_normalise(x_mnt, &x_exp);
01520 
01521     return fp64_round(x_sgn, x_exp, x_mnt << 1 | !!c, mode, flags);
01522 }

static void ArmISA::fp64_unpack ( int *  sgn,
int *  exp,
uint64_t *  mnt,
uint64_t  x,
int  mode,
int *  flags 
) [inline, static] 

00410 {
00411     *sgn = x >> 63;
00412     *exp = x >> 52 & 2047;
00413     *mnt = x & (((uint64_t)1 << 52) - 1);
00414 
00415     // Handle subnormals:
00416     if (*exp) {
00417         *mnt |= (uint64_t)1 << 52;
00418     } else {
00419         ++*exp;
00420         if ((mode & FPLIB_FZ) && *mnt) {
00421             *flags |= FPLIB_IDC;
00422             *mnt = 0;
00423         }
00424     }
00425 }

00312 {
00313     return fp64_pack(sgn, 0, 0);
00314 }

T2 ArmISA::fplibConvert ( T1  op,
FPRounding  rounding,
FPSCR &  fpscr 
) [inline]

Floating-point convert precision.

uint64_t fplibConvert ( uint16_t  op,
FPRounding  rounding,
FPSCR &  fpscr 
) [inline] 

01962 {
01963     int mode = modeConv(fpscr);
01964     int flags = 0;
01965     int sgn, exp;
01966     uint16_t mnt;
01967     uint64_t result;
01968 
01969     // Unpack floating-point operand optionally with flush-to-zero:
01970     fp16_unpack(&sgn, &exp, &mnt, op, mode, &flags);
01971 
01972     if (exp == 31 && !fpscr.ahp && (uint16_t)(mnt << 6)) {
01973         if (fpscr.dn) {
01974             result = fp64_defaultNaN();
01975         } else {
01976             result = fp64_FPConvertNaN_16(op);
01977         }
01978         if (!(mnt >> 9 & 1)) {
01979             flags |= FPLIB_IOC;
01980         }
01981     } else if (exp == 31 && !fpscr.ahp) {
01982         result = fp64_infinity(sgn);
01983     } else if (!mnt) {
01984         result = fp64_zero(sgn);
01985     } else {
01986         mnt = fp16_normalise(mnt, &exp);
01987         result = fp64_pack(sgn, exp - 15 + 1023 + 5, (uint64_t)mnt << 37);
01988     }
01989 
01990     set_fpscr0(fpscr, flags);
01991 
01992     return result;
01993 }

static T ArmISA::fpMax ( T  a,
T  b 
) [inline, static] 

00637 {

00640     if (std::isnan(b))

static T ArmISA::fpMaxNum ( T  a,
T  b 
) [inline, static] 

00620 {
00621     const bool     single = (sizeof(T) == sizeof(float));
00622     const uint64_t qnan   = single ? 0x7fc00000 : ULL(0x7ff8000000000000);
00623 
00624     if (std::isnan(a))
00625         return ((fpToBits(a) & qnan) == qnan) ? b : a;
00626     if (std::isnan(b))
00627         return ((fpToBits(b) & qnan) == qnan) ? a : b;
00628     // Handle comparisons of +0 and -0.
00629     if (!std::signbit(a) && std::signbit(b))
00630         return a;
00631     return fmax(a, b);
00632 };

static T ArmISA::fpMinNum ( T  a,
T  b 
) [inline, static] 

00648 {
00649     const bool     single = (sizeof(T) == sizeof(float));
00650     const uint64_t qnan   = single ? 0x7fc00000 : ULL(0x7ff8000000000000);

00654     if (std::isnan(b))

static T ArmISA::fpMulAdd ( T  op1,
T  op2,
T  addend 
) [inline, static] 

00587 {
00588     T result;
00589 
00590     if (sizeof(T) == sizeof(float))
00591         result = fmaf(op1, op2, addend);
00592     else
00593         result = fma(op1, op2, addend);
00594 
00595     // ARM doesn't generate signed nan's from this opperation, so fix up the result
00596     if (std::isnan(result) && !std::isnan(op1) &&
00597         !std::isnan(op2) && !std::isnan(addend))
00598     {
00599         uint64_t bitMask = ULL(0x1) << ((sizeof(T) * 8) - 1);
00600         result = bitsToFp(fpToBits(result) & ~bitMask, op1);
00601     }
00602     return result;
00603 }

static T ArmISA::fpMulX ( T  a,
T  b 
) [inline, static] 

00533 {
00534     uint64_t opData;
00535     uint32_t sign1;
00536     uint32_t sign2;
00537     const bool single = (sizeof(T) == sizeof(float));
00538     if (single) {
00539         opData = (fpToBits(a));
00540         sign1 = opData>>31;
00541         opData = (fpToBits(b));
00542         sign2 = opData>>31;
00543     } else {
00544         opData = (fpToBits(a));
00545         sign1 = opData>>63;
00546         opData = (fpToBits(b));
00547         sign2 = opData>>63;
00548     }
00549     bool inf1 = (std::fpclassify(a) == FP_INFINITE);
00550     bool inf2 = (std::fpclassify(b) == FP_INFINITE);
00551     bool zero1 = (std::fpclassify(a) == FP_ZERO);
00552     bool zero2 = (std::fpclassify(b) == FP_ZERO);
00553     if ((inf1 && zero2) || (zero1 && inf2)) {
00554         if(sign1 ^ sign2)
00555             return (T)(-2.0);
00556         else
00557             return (T)(2.0);
00558     } else {
00559         return (a * b);
00560     }
00561 };

float fpRecipEstimate ( FPSCR &  fpscr,
float  op 
)
static T ArmISA::fpRecps ( T  a,
T  b 
) [inline, static] 

00698 {
00699     int fpClassA = std::fpclassify(a);
00700     int fpClassB = std::fpclassify(b);
00701     T aXb;
00702     int fpClassAxB;
00703 
00704     if ((fpClassA == FP_ZERO && fpClassB == FP_INFINITE) ||
00705         (fpClassA == FP_INFINITE && fpClassB == FP_ZERO)) {
00706         return 2.0;
00707     }
00708     aXb = a*b;
00709     fpClassAxB = std::fpclassify(aXb);
00710     if(fpClassAxB == FP_SUBNORMAL) {
00711        feraiseexcept(FeUnderflow);
00712        return 2.0;
00713     }
00714     return 2.0 - (a * b);
00715 };

00748         (fpClassA == FP_INFINITE && fpClassB == FP_ZERO)) {

00750     }
00751     aXb = a*b;
00752     fpClassAxB = std::fpclassify(aXb);
00753     if(fpClassAxB == FP_SUBNORMAL) {
00754        feraiseexcept(FeUnderflow);

float fprSqrtEstimate ( FPSCR &  fpscr,
float  op 
)
static T ArmISA::fpRSqrts ( T  a,
T  b 
) [inline, static] 

00676 {
00677     int fpClassA = std::fpclassify(a);
00678     int fpClassB = std::fpclassify(b);
00679     T aXb;
00680     int fpClassAxB;
00681 
00682     if ((fpClassA == FP_ZERO && fpClassB == FP_INFINITE) ||
00683         (fpClassA == FP_INFINITE && fpClassB == FP_ZERO)) {
00684         return 1.5;
00685     }
00686     aXb = a*b;
00687     fpClassAxB = std::fpclassify(aXb);
00688     if(fpClassAxB == FP_SUBNORMAL) {
00689        feraiseexcept(FeUnderflow);
00690        return 1.5;
00691     }
00692     return (3.0 - (a * b)) / 2.0;
00693 };

static uint32_t ArmISA::FPToFixed_32 ( int  sgn,
int  exp,
uint64_t  mnt,
bool  u,
FPRounding  rounding,
int *  flags 
) [static] 

02915 {
02916     uint64_t x = FPToFixed_64(sgn, exp, mnt, u, rounding, flags);
02917     if (u ? x >= (uint64_t)1 << 32 :
02918         !(x < (uint64_t)1 << 31 ||
02919           (uint64_t)-x <= (uint64_t)1 << 31)) {
02920         *flags = FPLIB_IOC;
02921         x = ((uint32_t)!u << 31) - !sgn;
02922     }
02923     return x;
02924 }

static uint64_t ArmISA::FPToFixed_64 ( int  sgn,
int  exp,
uint64_t  mnt,
bool  u,
FPRounding  rounding,
int *  flags 
) [static] 

02867 {
02868     uint64_t x;
02869     int err;
02870 
02871     if (exp > 1023 + 63) {
02872         *flags = FPLIB_IOC;
02873         return ((uint64_t)!u << 63) - !sgn;
02874     }
02875 
02876     x = lsr64(mnt << 11, 1023 + 63 - exp);
02877     err = (exp > 1023 + 63 - 2 ? 0 :
02878            (lsr64(mnt << 11, 1023 + 63 - 2 - exp) & 3) |
02879            !!(mnt << 11 & (lsl64(1, 1023 + 63 - 2 - exp) - 1)));
02880 
02881     switch (rounding) {
02882       case FPRounding_TIEEVEN:
02883         x += (err == 3 || (err == 2 && (x & 1)));
02884         break;
02885       case FPRounding_POSINF:
02886         x += err && !sgn;
02887         break;
02888       case FPRounding_NEGINF:
02889         x += err && sgn;
02890         break;
02891       case FPRounding_ZERO:
02892         break;
02893       case FPRounding_TIEAWAY:
02894         x += err >> 1;
02895         break;
02896       default:
02897         assert(0);
02898     }
02899 
02900     if (u ? sgn && x : x > ((uint64_t)1 << 63) - !sgn) {
02901         *flags = FPLIB_IOC;
02902         return ((uint64_t)!u << 63) - !sgn;
02903     }
02904 
02905     if (err) {
02906         *flags = FPLIB_IXC;
02907     }
02908 
02909     return sgn ? -x : x;
02910 }

void ArmISA::handleLockedSnoop ( XC *  xc,
PacketPtr  pkt,
Addr  cacheBlockMask 
) [inline] 

00066 {
00067     DPRINTF(LLSC,"%s:  handleing snoop for address: %#x locked: %d\n",
00068             xc->getCpuPtr()->name(),pkt->getAddr(),
00069             xc->readMiscReg(MISCREG_LOCKFLAG));
00070     if (!xc->readMiscReg(MISCREG_LOCKFLAG))
00071         return;
00072 
00073     Addr locked_addr = xc->readMiscReg(MISCREG_LOCKADDR) & cacheBlockMask;
00074     // If no caches are attached, the snoop address always needs to be masked
00075     Addr snoop_addr = pkt->getAddr() & cacheBlockMask;
00076 
00077     DPRINTF(LLSC,"%s:  handleing snoop for address: %#x locked addr: %#x\n",
00078             xc->getCpuPtr()->name(),snoop_addr, locked_addr);
00079     if (locked_addr == snoop_addr) {
00080         DPRINTF(LLSC,"%s: address match, clearing lock and signaling sev\n",
00081                 xc->getCpuPtr()->name());
00082         xc->setMiscReg(MISCREG_LOCKFLAG, false);
00083         // Implement ARMv8 WFE/SEV semantics
00084         xc->setMiscReg(MISCREG_SEV_MAILBOX, true);
00085         xc->getCpuPtr()->wakeup();
00086     }
00087 }

void ArmISA::handleLockedSnoopHit ( XC *  xc  )  [inline] 

00102 {
00103     DPRINTF(LLSC,"%s:  handling snoop lock hit address: %#x\n",
00104             xc->getCpuPtr()->name(), xc->readMiscReg(MISCREG_LOCKADDR));
00105         xc->setMiscReg(MISCREG_LOCKFLAG, false);
00106         xc->setMiscReg(MISCREG_SEV_MAILBOX, true);
00107 }

bool ArmISA::handleLockedWrite ( XC *  xc,
Request *  req,
Addr  cacheBlockMask 
) [inline] 

00112 {
00113     if (req->isSwap())
00114         return true;
00115 
00116     DPRINTF(LLSC,"%s: handling locked write for  address %#x in monitor\n",
00117             xc->getCpuPtr()->name(), req->getPaddr());
00118     // Verify that the lock flag is still set and the address
00119     // is correct
00120     bool lock_flag = xc->readMiscReg(MISCREG_LOCKFLAG);
00121     Addr lock_addr = xc->readMiscReg(MISCREG_LOCKADDR) & cacheBlockMask;
00122     if (!lock_flag || (req->getPaddr() & cacheBlockMask) != lock_addr) {
00123         // Lock flag not set or addr mismatch in CPU;
00124         // don't even bother sending to memory system
00125         req->setExtraData(0);
00126         xc->setMiscReg(MISCREG_LOCKFLAG, false);
00127         DPRINTF(LLSC,"%s: clearing lock flag in handle locked write\n",
00128                 xc->getCpuPtr()->name());
00129         // the rest of this code is not architectural;
00130         // it's just a debugging aid to help detect
00131         // livelock by warning on long sequences of failed
00132         // store conditionals
00133         int stCondFailures = xc->readStCondFailures();
00134         stCondFailures++;
00135         xc->setStCondFailures(stCondFailures);
00136         if (stCondFailures % 100000 == 0) {
00137             warn("context %d: %d consecutive "
00138                  "store conditional failures\n",
00139                  xc->contextId(), stCondFailures);
00140         }
00141 
00142         // store conditional failed already, so don't issue it to mem
00143         return false;
00144     }
00145     return true;
00146 }

static void ArmISA::lsl128 ( uint64_t *  r0,
uint64_t *  r1,
uint64_t  x0,
uint64_t  x1,
uint32_t  shift 
) [inline, static] 

00103 {
00104     if (shift < 64) {
00105         *r1 = x1 << shift | x0 >> (64 - shift);
00106         *r0 = x0 << shift;
00107     } else if (shift < 128) {
00108         *r1 = x0 << (shift - 64);
00109         *r0 = 0;
00110     } else {
00111         *r1 = 0;
00112         *r0 = 0;
00113     }
00114 }

) [inline, static] 

00118 {

00121         *r1 = x1 >> shift;

00124         *r1 = 0;
00125     } else {
00126         *r0 = 0;

static IntRegIndex ArmISA::makeSP ( IntRegIndex  reg  )  [inline, static]

static uint32_t ArmISA::modified_imm ( uint8_t  ctrlImm,
uint8_t  dataImm 
) [inline, static] 

00059 {
00060     uint32_t bigData = dataImm;
00061     uint32_t bigCtrl = ctrlImm;
00062     if (bigCtrl < 4) {
00063         switch (bigCtrl) {
00064           case 0:
00065             return bigData;
00066           case 1:
00067             return bigData | (bigData << 16);
00068           case 2:
00069             return (bigData << 8) | (bigData << 24);
00070           case 3:
00071             return (bigData << 0) | (bigData << 8) |
00072                    (bigData << 16) | (bigData << 24);
00073         }
00074     }
00075     bigCtrl = (bigCtrl << 1) | ((bigData >> 7) & 0x1);
00076     bigData |= (1 << 7);
00077     return bigData << (32 - bigCtrl);
00078 }

static void ArmISA::mul62x62 ( uint64_t *  x0,
uint64_t *  x1,
uint64_t  a,
uint64_t  b 
) [inline, static] 

00133 {
00134     uint32_t mask = ((uint32_t)1 << 31) - 1;
00135     uint64_t a0 = a & mask;
00136     uint64_t a1 = a >> 31 & mask;
00137     uint64_t b0 = b & mask;
00138     uint64_t b1 = b >> 31 & mask;
00139     uint64_t p0 = a0 * b0;
00140     uint64_t p2 = a1 * b1;
00141     uint64_t p1 = (a0 + a1) * (b0 + b1) - p0 - p2;
00142     uint64_t s0 = p0;
00143     uint64_t s1 = (s0 >> 31) + p1;
00144     uint64_t s2 = (s1 >> 31) + p2;
00145     *x0 = (s0 & mask) | (s1 & mask) << 31 | s2 << 62;
00146     *x1 = s2 >> 2;
00147 }

static void ArmISA::mul64x32 ( uint64_t *  x0,
uint64_t *  x1,
uint64_t  a,
uint32_t  b 
) [inline, static] 

00151 {
00152     uint64_t t0 = (uint64_t)(uint32_t)a * b;
00153     uint64_t t1 = (t0 >> 32) + (a >> 32) * b;
00154     *x0 = t1 << 32 | (uint32_t)t0;
00155     *x1 = t1 >> 32;
00156 }

static void ArmISA::mul64x64 ( uint64_t *  x0,
uint64_t *  x1,
uint64_t  a,
uint64_t  b 
) [inline, static] 

00160 {
00161     uint64_t a0 = (uint32_t)a;
00162     uint64_t a1 = a >> 32;
00163     uint64_t b0 = (uint32_t)b;
00164     uint64_t b1 = b >> 32;
00165     uint64_t t1 = (a0 * b0 >> 32) + a1 * b0;
00166     uint64_t t2 = a0 * b1;
00167     uint64_t x = ((uint64_t)(uint32_t)t1 + (uint32_t)t2) >> 32;
00168     x += t1 >> 32;
00169     x += t2 >> 32;
00170     x += a1 * b1;
00171     *x0 = a * b;
00172     *x1 = x;
00173 }

00095 {
00096     // eSize must be less than 4:
00097     // 0 -> 8-bit elems,
00098     // 1 -> 16-bit elems,
00099     // 2 -> 32-bit elems,
00100     // 3 -> 64-bit elems

00102 
00103     XReg data;
00104 
00105     int eBits = 8 << eSize;

00107     assert(lsbPos < 128);
00108     int shiftAmt = lsbPos % 64;
00109 
00110     XReg maskBits = -1;
00111     if (eBits == 64) {
00112         maskBits = 0;
00113     } else {
00114         maskBits = maskBits << eBits;
00115     }
00116     maskBits = ~maskBits;
00117

00119         data = (src.lo >> shiftAmt) & maskBits;
00120     } else {
00121         data = (src.hi >> shiftAmt) & maskBits;
00122     }
00123     return data;

static double ArmISA::recipEstimate ( double  a  )  [static] 

00816 {

static double ArmISA::recipSqrtEstimate ( double  a  )  [static] 

00729 {
00730     int64_t q0, q1, s;
00731     double r;
00732     if (a < 0.5) {
00733         q0 = (int64_t)(a * 512.0);
00734         r = 1.0 / sqrt(((double)q0 + 0.5) / 512.0);
00735     } else {
00736         q1 = (int64_t)(a * 256.0);
00737         r = 1.0 / sqrt(((double)q1 + 0.5) / 256.0);
00738     }
00739     s = (int64_t)(256.0 * r + 0.5);
00740     return (double)s / 256.0;
00741 }

static uint64_t ArmISA::simd_modified_imm ( bool  op,
uint8_t  cmode,
uint8_t  data,
bool &  immValid,
bool  isAarch64 = false 
) [inline, static] 

00083 {
00084     uint64_t bigData = data;
00085     immValid = true;
00086     switch (cmode) {
00087       case 0x0:
00088       case 0x1:
00089         bigData = (bigData << 0) | (bigData << 32);
00090         break;
00091       case 0x2:
00092       case 0x3:
00093         bigData = (bigData << 8) | (bigData << 40);
00094         break;
00095       case 0x4:
00096       case 0x5:
00097         bigData = (bigData << 16) | (bigData << 48);
00098         break;
00099       case 0x6:
00100       case 0x7:
00101         bigData = (bigData << 24) | (bigData << 56);
00102         break;
00103       case 0x8:
00104       case 0x9:
00105         bigData = (bigData << 0) | (bigData << 16) |
00106                   (bigData << 32) | (bigData << 48);
00107         break;
00108       case 0xa:
00109       case 0xb:
00110         bigData = (bigData << 8) | (bigData << 24) |
00111                   (bigData << 40) | (bigData << 56);
00112         break;
00113       case 0xc:
00114         bigData = (0xffULL << 0) | (bigData << 8) |
00115                   (0xffULL << 32) | (bigData << 40);
00116         break;
00117       case 0xd:
00118         bigData = (0xffffULL << 0) | (bigData << 16) |
00119                   (0xffffULL << 32) | (bigData << 48);
00120         break;
00121       case 0xe:
00122         if (op) {
00123             bigData = 0;
00124             for (int i = 7; i >= 0; i--) {
00125                 if (bits(data, i)) {
00126                     bigData |= (ULL(0xFF) << (i * 8));
00127                 }
00128             }
00129         } else {
00130             bigData = (bigData << 0)  | (bigData << 8)  |
00131                       (bigData << 16) | (bigData << 24) |
00132                       (bigData << 32) | (bigData << 40) |
00133                       (bigData << 48) | (bigData << 56);
00134         }
00135         break;
00136       case 0xf:
00137         {
00138             uint64_t bVal = 0;
00139             if (!op) {
00140                 bVal = bits(bigData, 6) ? (0x1F) : (0x20);
00141                 bigData = (bits(bigData, 5, 0) << 19) |
00142                           (bVal << 25) | (bits(bigData, 7) << 31);
00143                 bigData |= (bigData << 32);
00144                 break;
00145             } else if (isAarch64) {
00146                 bVal = bits(bigData, 6) ? (0x0FF) : (0x100);
00147                 bigData = (bits(bigData, 5, 0) << 48) |
00148                           (bVal << 54) | (bits(bigData, 7) << 63);
00149                 break;
00150             }
00151         }
00152         // Fall through, immediate encoding is invalid.
00153       default:
00154         immValid = false;
00155         break;
00156     }
00157     return bigData;
00158 }

bool ArmISA::testPredicate ( uint32_t  nz,
uint32_t  c,
uint32_t  v,
ConditionCode  code 
) [inline] 

00071 {
00072     bool n = (nz & 0x2);
00073     bool z = (nz & 0x1);
00074 
00075     switch (code)
00076     {
00077         case COND_EQ: return  z;
00078         case COND_NE: return !z;
00079         case COND_CS: return  c;
00080         case COND_CC: return !c;
00081         case COND_MI: return  n;
00082         case COND_PL: return !n;
00083         case COND_VS: return  v;
00084         case COND_VC: return !v;
00085         case COND_HI: return  (c && !z);
00086         case COND_LS: return !(c && !z);
00087         case COND_GE: return !(n ^ v);
00088         case COND_LT: return  (n ^ v);
00089         case COND_GT: return !(n ^ v || z);
00090         case COND_LE: return  (n ^ v || z);
00091         case COND_AL: return true;
00092         case COND_UC: return true;
00093         default:
00094             panic("Unhandled predicate condition: %d\n", code);
00095     }
00096 }

uint16_t vcvtFpDFpH ( FPSCR &  fpscr,
bool  flush,
bool  defaultNan,
uint32_t  rMode,
bool  ahp,
double  op 
)
static uint16_t ArmISA::vcvtFpFpH ( FPSCR &  fpscr,
bool  flush,
bool  defaultNan,
uint32_t  rMode,
bool  ahp,
uint64_t  opBits,
bool  isDouble 
) [inline, static] 

00382 {
00383     uint32_t mWidth;
00384     uint32_t eWidth;
00385     uint32_t eHalfRange;
00386     uint32_t sBitPos;
00387 
00388     if (isDouble) {
00389         mWidth = 52;
00390         eWidth = 11;
00391     } else {
00392         mWidth = 23;
00393         eWidth = 8;
00394     }
00395     sBitPos    = eWidth + mWidth;
00396     eHalfRange = (1 << (eWidth-1)) - 1;
00397 
00398     // Extract the operand.
00399     bool neg = bits(opBits, sBitPos);
00400     uint32_t exponent = bits(opBits, sBitPos-1, mWidth);
00401     uint64_t oldMantissa = bits(opBits, mWidth-1, 0);
00402     uint32_t mantissa = oldMantissa >> (mWidth - 10);
00403     // Do the conversion.
00404     uint64_t extra = oldMantissa & mask(mWidth - 10);
00405     if (exponent == mask(eWidth)) {
00406         if (oldMantissa != 0) {
00407             // Nans.
00408             if (bits(mantissa, 9) == 0) {
00409                 // Signalling nan.
00410                 fpscr.ioc = 1;
00411             }
00412             if (ahp) {
00413                 mantissa = 0;
00414                 exponent = 0;
00415                 fpscr.ioc = 1;
00416             } else if (defaultNan) {
00417                 mantissa = (1 << 9);
00418                 exponent = 0x1f;
00419                 neg = false;
00420             } else {
00421                 exponent = 0x1f;
00422                 mantissa |= (1 << 9);
00423             }
00424         } else {
00425             // Infinities.
00426             exponent = 0x1F;
00427             if (ahp) {
00428                 fpscr.ioc = 1;
00429                 mantissa = 0x3ff;
00430             } else {
00431                 mantissa = 0;
00432             }
00433         }
00434     } else if (exponent == 0 && oldMantissa == 0) {
00435         // Zero, don't need to do anything.
00436     } else {
00437         // Normalized or denormalized numbers.
00438 
00439         bool inexact = (extra != 0);
00440 
00441         if (exponent == 0) {
00442             // Denormalized.
00443             // If flush to zero is on, this shouldn't happen.
00444             assert(!flush);
00445 
00446             // Check for underflow
00447             if (inexact || fpscr.ufe)
00448                 fpscr.ufc = 1;
00449 
00450             // Handle rounding.
00451             unsigned mode = rMode;
00452             if ((mode == VfpRoundUpward && !neg && extra) ||
00453                 (mode == VfpRoundDown && neg && extra) ||
00454                 (mode == VfpRoundNearest &&
00455                  (extra > (1 << 9) ||
00456                   (extra == (1 << 9) && bits(mantissa, 0))))) {
00457                 mantissa++;
00458             }
00459 
00460             // See if the number became normalized after rounding.
00461             if (mantissa == (1 << 10)) {
00462                 mantissa = 0;
00463                 exponent = 1;
00464             }
00465         } else {
00466             // Normalized.
00467 
00468             // We need to track the dropped bits differently since
00469             // more can be dropped by denormalizing.
00470             bool topOne = bits(extra, mWidth - 10 - 1);
00471             bool restZeros = bits(extra, mWidth - 10 - 2, 0) == 0;
00472 
00473             if (exponent <= (eHalfRange - 15)) {
00474                 // The result is too small. Denormalize.
00475                 mantissa |= (1 << 10);
00476                 while (mantissa && exponent <= (eHalfRange - 15)) {
00477                     restZeros = restZeros && !topOne;
00478                     topOne = bits(mantissa, 0);
00479                     mantissa = mantissa >> 1;
00480                     exponent++;
00481                 }
00482                 if (topOne || !restZeros)
00483                     inexact = true;
00484                 exponent = 0;
00485             } else {
00486                 // Change bias.
00487                 exponent -= (eHalfRange - 15);
00488             }
00489 
00490             if (exponent == 0 && (inexact || fpscr.ufe)) {
00491                 // Underflow
00492                 fpscr.ufc = 1;
00493             }
00494 
00495             // Handle rounding.
00496             unsigned mode = rMode;
00497             bool nonZero = topOne || !restZeros;
00498             if ((mode == VfpRoundUpward && !neg && nonZero) ||
00499                 (mode == VfpRoundDown && neg && nonZero) ||
00500                 (mode == VfpRoundNearest && topOne &&
00501                  (!restZeros || bits(mantissa, 0)))) {
00502                 mantissa++;
00503             }
00504 
00505             // See if we rounded up and need to bump the exponent.
00506             if (mantissa == (1 << 10)) {
00507                 mantissa = 0;
00508                 exponent++;
00509             }
00510 
00511             // Deal with overflow
00512             if (ahp) {
00513                 if (exponent >= 0x20) {
00514                     exponent = 0x1f;
00515                     mantissa = 0x3ff;
00516                     fpscr.ioc = 1;
00517                     // Supress inexact exception.
00518                     inexact = false;
00519                 }
00520             } else {
00521                 if (exponent >= 0x1f) {
00522                     if ((mode == VfpRoundNearest) ||
00523                         (mode == VfpRoundUpward && !neg) ||
00524                         (mode == VfpRoundDown && neg)) {
00525                         // Overflow to infinity.
00526                         exponent = 0x1f;
00527                         mantissa = 0;
00528                     } else {
00529                         // Overflow to max normal.
00530                         exponent = 0x1e;
00531                         mantissa = 0x3ff;
00532                     }
00533                     fpscr.ofc = 1;
00534                     inexact = true;
00535                 }
00536             }
00537         }
00538 
00539         if (inexact) {
00540             fpscr.ixc = 1;
00541         }
00542     }
00543     // Reassemble and install the result.
00544     uint32_t result = bits(mantissa, 9, 0);
00545     replaceBits(result, 14, 10, exponent);
00546     if (neg)
00547         result |= (1 << 15);
00548     return result;
00549 }

static uint64_t ArmISA::vcvtFpHFp ( FPSCR &  fpscr,
bool  defaultNan,
bool  ahp,
uint16_t  op,
bool  isDouble 
) [inline, static] 

00569 {
00570     uint32_t mWidth;
00571     uint32_t eWidth;
00572     uint32_t eHalfRange;
00573     uint32_t sBitPos;
00574 
00575     if (isDouble) {
00576         mWidth = 52;
00577         eWidth = 11;
00578     } else {
00579         mWidth = 23;
00580         eWidth = 8;
00581     }
00582     sBitPos    = eWidth + mWidth;
00583     eHalfRange = (1 << (eWidth-1)) - 1;
00584 
00585     // Extract the bitfields.
00586     bool neg = bits(op, 15);
00587     uint32_t exponent = bits(op, 14, 10);
00588     uint64_t mantissa = bits(op, 9, 0);
00589     // Do the conversion.
00590     if (exponent == 0) {
00591         if (mantissa != 0) {
00592             // Normalize the value.
00593             exponent = exponent + (eHalfRange - 15) + 1;
00594             while (mantissa < (1 << 10)) {
00595                 mantissa = mantissa << 1;
00596                 exponent--;
00597             }
00598         }
00599         mantissa = mantissa << (mWidth - 10);
00600     } else if (exponent == 0x1f && !ahp) {
00601         // Infinities and nans.
00602         exponent = mask(eWidth);
00603         if (mantissa != 0) {
00604             // Nans.
00605             mantissa = mantissa << (mWidth - 10);
00606             if (bits(mantissa, mWidth-1) == 0) {
00607                 // Signalling nan.
00608                 fpscr.ioc = 1;
00609                 mantissa |= (((uint64_t) 1) << (mWidth-1));
00610             }
00611             if (defaultNan) {
00612                 mantissa &= ~mask(mWidth-1);
00613                 neg = false;
00614             }
00615         }
00616     } else {
00617         exponent = exponent + (eHalfRange - 15);
00618         mantissa = mantissa << (mWidth - 10);
00619     }
00620     // Reassemble the result.
00621     uint64_t result = bits(mantissa, mWidth-1, 0);
00622     replaceBits(result, sBitPos-1, mWidth, exponent);
00623     if (neg) {
00624         result |= (((uint64_t) 1) << sBitPos);
00625     }
00626     return result;
00627 }

static uint64_t ArmISA::vfp_modified_imm ( uint8_t  data,
bool  wide 
) [inline, static] 

00162 {
00163     uint64_t bigData = data;
00164     uint64_t repData;
00165     if (wide) {
00166         repData = bits(data, 6) ? 0xFF : 0;
00167         bigData = (bits(bigData, 5, 0) << 48) |
00168                   (repData << 54) | (bits(~bigData, 6) << 62) |
00169                   (bits(bigData, 7) << 63);
00170     } else {
00171         repData = bits(data, 6) ? 0x1F : 0;
00172         bigData = (bits(bigData, 5, 0) << 19) |
00173                   (repData << 25) | (bits(~bigData, 6) << 30) |
00174                   (bits(bigData, 7) << 31);
00175     }
00176     return bigData;
00177 }

uint64_t ArmISA::vfpFpToFixed ( T  val,
bool  isSigned,
uint8_t  width,
uint8_t  imm,
bool  useRmode = true,
VfpRoundingMode  roundMode = VfpRoundZero,
bool  aarch64 = false 
) [inline] 

00268 {
00269     int  rmode;
00270     bool roundAwayFix = false;
00271 
00272     if (!useRmode) {
00273         rmode = fegetround();
00274     } else {
00275         switch (roundMode)
00276         {
00277           case VfpRoundNearest:
00278             rmode = FeRoundNearest;
00279             break;
00280           case VfpRoundUpward:
00281             rmode = FeRoundUpward;
00282             break;
00283           case VfpRoundDown:
00284             rmode = FeRoundDown;
00285             break;
00286           case VfpRoundZero:
00287             rmode = FeRoundZero;
00288             break;
00289           case VfpRoundAway:
00290             // There is no equivalent rounding mode, use round down and we'll
00291             // fix it later
00292             rmode        = FeRoundDown;
00293             roundAwayFix = true;
00294             break;
00295           default:
00296             panic("Unsupported roundMode %d\n", roundMode);
00297         }
00298     }
00299     __asm__ __volatile__("" : "=m" (rmode) : "m" (rmode));
00300     fesetround(FeRoundNearest);
00301     val = val * pow(2.0, imm);
00302     __asm__ __volatile__("" : "=m" (val) : "m" (val));
00303     fesetround(rmode);
00304     feclearexcept(FeAllExceptions);
00305     __asm__ __volatile__("" : "=m" (val) : "m" (val));
00306     T origVal = val;
00307     val = rint(val);
00308     __asm__ __volatile__("" : "=m" (val) : "m" (val));
00309 
00310     int exceptions = fetestexcept(FeAllExceptions);
00311 
00312     int fpType = std::fpclassify(val);
00313     if (fpType == FP_SUBNORMAL || fpType == FP_NAN) {
00314         if (fpType == FP_NAN) {
00315             exceptions |= FeInvalid;
00316         }
00317         val = 0.0;
00318     } else if (origVal != val) {
00319         switch (rmode) {
00320           case FeRoundNearest:
00321             if (origVal - val > 0.5)
00322                 val += 1.0;
00323             else if (val - origVal > 0.5)
00324                 val -= 1.0;
00325             break;
00326           case FeRoundDown:
00327             if (roundAwayFix) {
00328                 // The ordering on the subtraction looks a bit odd in that we
00329                 // don't do the obvious origVal - val, instead we do
00330                 // -(val - origVal). This is required to get the corruct bit
00331                 // exact behaviour when very close to the 0.5 threshold.
00332                 volatile T error = val;
00333                 error -= origVal;
00334                 error = -error;
00335                 if ( (error >  0.5) ||
00336                     ((error == 0.5) && (val >= 0)) )
00337                     val += 1.0;
00338             } else {
00339                 if (origVal < val)
00340                     val -= 1.0;
00341             }
00342             break;
00343           case FeRoundUpward:
00344             if (origVal > val)
00345                 val += 1.0;
00346             break;
00347         }
00348         exceptions |= FeInexact;
00349     }
00350 
00351     __asm__ __volatile__("" : "=m" (val) : "m" (val));
00352 
00353     if (isSigned) {
00354         bool     outOfRange = false;
00355         int64_t  result     = (int64_t) val;
00356         uint64_t finalVal;
00357 
00358         if (!aarch64) {
00359             if (width == 16) {
00360                 finalVal = (int16_t)val;
00361             } else if (width == 32) {
00362                 finalVal =(int32_t)val;
00363             } else if (width == 64) {
00364                 finalVal = result;
00365             } else {
00366                 panic("Unsupported width %d\n", width);
00367             }
00368 
00369             // check if value is in range
00370             int64_t minVal = ~mask(width-1);
00371             if ((double)val < minVal) {
00372                 outOfRange = true;
00373                 finalVal = minVal;
00374             }
00375             int64_t maxVal = mask(width-1);
00376             if ((double)val > maxVal) {
00377                 outOfRange = true;
00378                 finalVal = maxVal;
00379             }
00380         } else {
00381             bool isNeg = val < 0;
00382             finalVal = result & mask(width);
00383             // If the result is supposed to be less than 64 bits check that the
00384             // upper bits that got thrown away are just sign extension bits
00385             if (width != 64) {
00386                 outOfRange = ((uint64_t) result >> (width - 1)) !=
00387                              (isNeg ? mask(64-width+1) : 0);
00388             }
00389             // Check if the original floating point value doesn't matches the
00390             // integer version we are also out of range. So create a saturated
00391             // result.
00392             if (isNeg) {
00393                 outOfRange |= val < result;
00394                 if (outOfRange) {
00395                     finalVal = 1LL << (width-1);
00396                 }
00397             } else {
00398                 outOfRange |= val > result;
00399                 if (outOfRange) {
00400                     finalVal = mask(width-1);
00401                 }
00402             }
00403         }
00404 
00405         // Raise an exception if the value was out of range
00406         if (outOfRange) {
00407             exceptions |= FeInvalid;
00408             exceptions &= ~FeInexact;
00409         }
00410         setFPExceptions(exceptions);
00411         return finalVal;
00412     } else {
00413         if ((double)val < 0) {
00414             exceptions |= FeInvalid;
00415             exceptions &= ~FeInexact;
00416             setFPExceptions(exceptions);
00417             return 0;
00418         }
00419 
00420         uint64_t result = ((uint64_t) val) & mask(width);
00421         if (val > result) {
00422             exceptions |= FeInvalid;
00423             exceptions &= ~FeInexact;
00424             setFPExceptions(exceptions);
00425             return mask(width);
00426         }
00427 
00428         setFPExceptions(exceptions);
00429         return result;
00430     }
00431 };

Addr vtophys ( ThreadContext *  tc,
Addr  vaddr 
) 

00068 {
00069     Fault fault;
00070     // Set up a functional memory Request to pass to the TLB
00071     // to get it to translate the vaddr to a paddr
00072     Request req(0, addr, 64, 0x40, -1, 0, 0, 0);
00073     ArmISA::TLB *tlb;
00074 
00075     // Check the TLBs for a translation
00076     // It's possible that there is a valid translation in the tlb
00077     // that is no loger valid in the page table in memory
00078     // so we need to check here first
00079     //
00080     // Calling translateFunctional invokes a table-walk if required
00081     // so we should always succeed
00082     tlb = static_cast<ArmISA::TLB*>(tc->getDTBPtr());
00083     fault = tlb->translateFunctional(&req, tc, BaseTLB::Read, TLB::NormalTran);
00084     if (fault == NoFault)
00085         return req.getPaddr();
00086 
00087     tlb = static_cast<ArmISA::TLB*>(tc->getITBPtr());
00088     fault = tlb->translateFunctional(&req, tc, BaseTLB::Read, TLB::NormalTran);
00089     if (fault == NoFault)
00090         return req.getPaddr();
00091 
00092     panic("Table walkers support functional accesses. We should never get here\n");
00093 }

void ArmISA::writeVecElem ( VReg *  dest,
XReg  src,
int  index,
int  eSize 
) [inline]

Write a single NEON vector element leaving the others untouched. 

00061 {
00062     // eSize must be less than 4:
00063     // 0 -> 8-bit elems,
00064     // 1 -> 16-bit elems,
00065     // 2 -> 32-bit elems,
00066     // 3 -> 64-bit elems
00067     assert(eSize <= 3);
00068 
00069     int eBits = 8 << eSize;
00070     int lsbPos = index * eBits;
00071     assert(lsbPos < 128);
00072     int shiftAmt = lsbPos % 64;
00073 
00074     XReg maskBits = -1;
00075     if (eBits == 64) {
00076         maskBits = 0;
00077     } else {
00078         maskBits = maskBits << eBits;
00079     }
00080     maskBits = ~maskBits;
00081 
00082     XReg sMask = maskBits;
00083     maskBits = sMask << shiftAmt;
00084 
00085     if (lsbPos < 64) {
00086         dest->lo = (dest->lo & (~maskBits)) | ((src & sMask) << shiftAmt);
00087     } else {
00088         dest->hi = (dest->hi & (~maskBits)) | ((src & sMask) << shiftAmt);
00089     }

Bitfield<9> uma
int unflattenResultMiscReg[NUM_MISCREGS]

If the reg is a child reg of a banked set, then the parent is the last banked one in the list. This is messy, and the wish is to eventually have the bitmap replaced with a better data structure. the preUnflatten function initializes a lookup table to speed up the search for these banked registers.
